1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with motion planning, which is a core problem in robotics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a method for accelerating planning while preserving optimality, which is a common problem in AI. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with control of systems (robots) in continuous state spaces. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper uses angelic semantics, which is a programming language concept. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses local metric and topological properties of the problem domain, which are common in machine learning.
